<title>Selection of Data Intensive Projects</title>
</head>
<ul>
	<li>Customer Value Management for a leading Bank. Development of propensity models for client behaviour based on data from multiple sources (including SAP and various product-related data repositories). Project in the 2008-2009 period.</li>
	<li>Performance Monitoring and Target Setting for the branches of a leading Bank. Development of a platform that consolidates data from multiple sources and synthesises them with different ranking models. Recurring engagements in the 2001-2009 period.</li>
	<li>Retail Credit Underwriting for a mid-sized Bank including the redesign of processes and the introduction of decision support systems to improve credit risk control and regulatory compliance based on scoring algorithms. Project in the 2003-2004 period.</li>
  <li>Credit Function Reform for  a leading Bank. Centralisation of decision taking processes and development of credit risk assessment models for business loans. Project in the 1999-2002 period.</li>
  <li>Assessment of branch network capabilities and branch performance evaluation using multicriteria data analysis. Project during 1999.</li>
</ul>
